{
  "stem": "10359.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it took quite a few years-- about 50 or so years-- to establish a new community, Jewish community, in Ostrog.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "After that, we still had some little, what you call pogroms.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But the Tatars, which were lived in our area, helped the Jews at that time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then in the 16-- in the 1700s and 1800s, Ostrog had about 10,000 or more Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the, the Jewish community prospered very well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was the center of the Hasidic community and all the schools and all of Poland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the more prominent rabbis from all of Poland were-- came to lecture and to teach at the yeshivas in Ostrog.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Then we also had a lot of Zionist organizations, about six or seven of them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Everybody had different uniforms.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They felt very free.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And this was the golden age-- so to say, up to '39-- of the Jews in Ostrog because they paraded in their uniforms.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They felt very free to express their nationalistic feelings.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So everything was fine until the Soviets came in and disband all of this, and then the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And after the Soviets came, naturally, everything changed because you couldn't have any businesses, even though my stepmother was still had the-- she was still alive.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And she still continued to work in that drugstore that my father had.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But then gradually, they closed all those stores because they considered them being capitalistic.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And then it was very hard financially because we only had what we could either sell, you know, [INAUDIBLE], so to say, or exchange different cosmetics or medication products for eggs or butter or bread.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
